The paper deals with a network design problem and presents distributed algorithms for it. This suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The problem involves graphs and trees, indicating that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The algorithms presented involve approximation ratios, which suggests that it could belong to the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category. The problem also involves connectivity, which could place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT) sub-category.
